And I don't think the servants were upset that they got tasked with getting the cars there probably like, this is all

43:56.656 --> 43:59.639
I just want to be part of something in any way.

43:59.659 --> 44:05.185
And I'll say that when it comes to missions again, by the way, what am I going to do?

44:05.305 --> 44:06.466
Just show up.

44:06.486 --> 44:11.551
You know, just, you know, just steer one of the carts.

44:11.831 --> 44:14.354
I don't know what I'm going to do, but I'm going to be there.

44:14.874 --> 44:23.083
And I know when we went to Nepal, the last time Renee was in a couple gals, we're going to teach a woman's conference.

44:23.563 --> 44:26.386
And I was like, man, I'll just be happy to carry the suitcases.

44:26.626 --> 44:30.771
And I would kind of, I can carry your suitcases to bless you while you get to teach.

44:30.811 --> 44:31.312
And you know what?

44:31.332 --> 44:33.134
God then decided, well, you know what, right?

44:33.154 --> 44:36.618
I'm gonna send you back and now you're gonna do this and you're gonna do that.

44:36.678 --> 44:38.601
And so just the beauty that we see.

44:39.021 --> 44:49.694
But now verse 21 and 22, then the sons of Israel did so and Joseph gave them carts according to the command of Pharaoh and he gave them provisions for the journey.

44:49.754 --> 44:52.658
He gave to all of them

44:52.930 --> 45:00.942
to each man changes of garments, but the Benjamin, he gave 300 pieces of silver and five changes of garments.

45:01.542 --> 45:04.206
Verse 21 still shows us something in it.

45:04.226 --> 45:08.793
He's second in command, but he's still under the command of Pharaoh.

45:09.274 --> 45:12.338
He didn't get to make his own choices of

45:12.482 --> 45:13.783
what he wanted to do.

45:13.843 --> 45:17.507
It was still under Pharaoh, which is an interesting thought upon that.

45:17.567 --> 45:25.415
But he gave five, each man a change of garment, but Benjamin, he gave five changes, plus 300 pieces of silver.

45:25.455 --> 45:26.496
And you know what?

45:26.536 --> 45:27.497
The boys don't blink.

45:28.378 --> 45:29.078
And you know why?

45:29.098 --> 45:34.964
Forgiveness forgets fairness.

45:36.105 --> 45:41.170
When you're forgiven, you could care less what any of the world considers fair.

45:41.538 --> 45:42.321
You know what's fair?

45:42.623 --> 45:43.707
Everybody gets five.

45:44.109 --> 45:44.873
You know what's fair?

45:45.093 --> 45:45.977
Everybody gets 300.

45:46.058 --> 45:50.738
But when you've been forgiven, you go, all I care is that I'm forgiven.

45:51.298 --> 45:52.660
I don't care what happens.

45:53.121 --> 45:57.689
I don't care the blessings and the prosperity or anything else that happens to anyone else.

45:58.130 --> 46:00.013
All that I care is that I'm forgiven.

46:00.033 --> 46:02.658
And when you're blessed, I ain't looking at fairness.

46:02.798 --> 46:04.541
I'm just looking at praise the Lord.

46:04.622 --> 46:09.029
You're being blessed by the one who forgave you as well.

46:09.530 --> 46:13.938
In verse 23 and 24, word for us, church, don't faint.

46:14.274 --> 46:15.217
We're almost home.

46:15.618 --> 46:17.743
Don't hold back verse 23 and 24.

46:18.024 --> 46:24.722
And he sent to his father these things, 10 donkeys loaded with goods, good things of Egypt.

46:25.794 --> 46:31.524
In 10 female donkeys loaded with green, bread, and food for his father for the journey.

46:31.885 --> 46:38.316
Verse 24, so he sent his brothers away and they departed and he said to them, see that you do not become troubled.

46:38.857 --> 46:42.163
Maybe your translation says, faint along the way.

46:42.664 --> 46:45.168
And Joseph is simply saying, you're almost there.

46:45.729 --> 46:48.434
Look, don't leave here and start

46:49.090 --> 46:51.633
Bickering over, I can't believe we did this.

46:51.693 --> 46:54.377
Just leave here in the joy of your forgiveness.

46:54.837 --> 46:59.524
But also, I just love the word of don't faint.

47:00.525 --> 47:02.087
Church, we're almost home.

47:02.768 --> 47:05.652
And I just want to encourage you, we're not home.

47:06.272 --> 47:16.786
And let us not get entangled by the cares of the world, get entangled by the things that distract

47:17.122 --> 47:21.006
It's okay to have hobbies and enjoy this and these type of things.

47:21.387 --> 47:24.810
You know, I'm not saying that, but we're almost home.

47:24.871 --> 47:27.614
This is not the time to look back.

47:28.134 --> 47:37.404
It's the time to keep our eyes on the cross, keep pressing through because we still got other people that we need to go and get and bring back with us.

47:37.805 --> 47:38.866
And that's what's happening.

47:39.246 --> 47:44.492
Go get the family and bring them down because there's five more years to go.

47:44.552 --> 47:46.194
Verse 25.

47:46.690 --> 47:52.238
Then they went up to Egypt and came to the land of Canaan to Jacob their father.

47:52.258 --> 47:53.139
That's three weeks.

47:53.199 --> 47:55.442
So lots of time to argue and bicker.

47:55.502 --> 47:56.824
And he's saying, don't do it.

47:57.645 --> 47:59.728
Just go get the family and get back here.

47:59.848 --> 48:01.090
Verse 26 through 28.

48:01.290 --> 48:07.119
And they told him saying, Joseph is still alive.

48:09.542 --> 48:11.264
Think of that after 22 years.

48:12.146 --> 48:15.250
And this stages us for next week's message.

48:16.194 --> 48:23.861
And he is governor over all the land of Egypt, and Jacob's heart stood still because he did not believe him.

48:25.503 --> 48:27.365
That word, heart stood still.

48:27.785 --> 48:30.547
I couldn't get to the bottom of it, to be honest with you.

48:33.370 --> 48:34.511
It means what it means.

48:34.571 --> 48:35.652
I don't think it's poetic.

48:37.054 --> 48:39.456
Did his heart literally stop?

48:40.557 --> 48:43.319
Did he have a stroke, a heart attack?

48:45.141 --> 48:46.002
Whatever it is,

48:46.082 --> 48:49.951
his heart stood still because he didn't believe it.

48:50.172 --> 48:52.056
And I could see after 22 years.

48:53.099 --> 48:58.913
But when they told him all these words which Joseph had said to them and when he saw the card.

48:58.933 --> 49:04.466
So all this that Joseph's given we would logically go, you just need enough food to get up.

49:05.346 --> 49:08.952
to feed the people along the way, to feed your animal, then get your herd and bring it back.

49:09.413 --> 49:20.851
What's up with the gold to change the clothes and all these fine things from Egypt because Joseph is bolstering the unbelief that he knows Jacob, his father's going to go, I can't believe it.

49:21.472 --> 49:27.442
But then he's going to look up and see the cards and go, there has to be something more behind this.

49:27.842 --> 49:36.271
But when they told him all the words, Joseph had said to them, and when he saw the cards, which Joseph had sent carrying, the spirit of Jacob, their father revived.

49:36.772 --> 49:39.615
Verse 28, then Israel said, it is enough.

49:40.316 --> 49:41.877
Joseph, my son, is still alive.

49:42.138 --> 49:45.622
I will go and see him before I die.

49:45.682 --> 49:56.914
And I just want to close with, well, right on time, what heartache.

49:58.082 --> 50:00.565
We put ourselves in his place.

50:00.825 --> 50:01.707
What pain?

50:02.047 --> 50:02.247
What?

50:02.868 --> 50:05.531
22 years of thinking my son was destroyed.

50:06.112 --> 50:08.095
And you know, Jacob, he'd be like the rest of it.

50:08.115 --> 50:09.156
If only I didn't send him.

50:09.216 --> 50:15.003
If I did not send my Joseph to go check on the brothers, none of this would have happened.

50:15.043 --> 50:16.085
This is all on me.

50:17.446 --> 50:24.956
But 22 years of the pain, thinking that he was destroyed by a wild beast and all these type of things.

50:25.316 --> 50:26.738
And he says, I'll go.

50:27.714 --> 50:28.996
I'm 130 years old.

50:29.016 --> 50:34.103
This is a long ride for me, but I will go at whatever it takes to get down and see my boy.

50:34.123 --> 50:36.546
Again, Joseph can't go.

50:36.566 --> 50:37.327
He's under command.

50:39.329 --> 50:41.572
Whatever it takes, I'm getting there, Joseph.

50:41.613 --> 50:43.595
Make sure that the bride is prepared.

50:43.635 --> 50:44.296
Here's the cards.

50:44.336 --> 50:45.398
Make sure he gets here.

50:48.462 --> 50:57.714
And all I want to disclose with for you for hope for all of us is, this verse kind of reminds me of

50:58.850 --> 51:21.927
Jesus, his first miracle with the marriage feast, brings out the wine, all the wine is gone, turns water in the wine, the master of the feast comes out and he said, every man at the beginning sets out the good wine and when the guests have well drunk, then the inferior, you have kept the good wine until now.

51:22.508 --> 51:26.514
And I just want to encourage you, even if life has been wonderful,

51:27.842 --> 51:35.950
But maybe you've been hurt or your heart has been, you know, just ached by things that have happened in your life.

51:37.091 --> 51:39.813
There is no pain that God can heal.

51:42.536 --> 51:57.010
And more so, when reconciliation comes, and if you will step in to free them by forgiveness and you run to reconciliation, I will tell you

51:57.314 --> 52:01.539
Because it's the heart of God, He can save the best for last.

52:02.220 --> 52:13.795
And all of the pain of 22 years, even if it was only 22 months left, He can take that and make those 22 months greater than the whole summation of the life before.

52:15.276 --> 52:19.762
But there's a piece that we come and we say,

52:20.002 --> 52:21.504
I'm going to free them with forgiveness.

52:21.604 --> 52:23.708
I'm going to run to the reconciliation.

52:24.188 --> 52:30.578
If I was the offending party, I am just going to ask for mercy to be come upon me.

52:30.638 --> 52:34.104
And then we come and go, here we are back together.

52:34.164 --> 52:38.590
Let's live like there is no tomorrow.

52:38.971 --> 52:43.538
Let's live for the day that we have today together.

52:44.578 --> 52:46.580
Father, we bless you and we thank you.

52:46.661 --> 52:47.742
What a word.

52:47.802 --> 52:50.866
We read a narrative and we just see an amazing heart of God.

52:50.886 --> 52:55.972
And I thank you how you opened this for us to see your heart and you illuminated.

52:56.012 --> 52:58.174
Who is our God?

52:58.214 --> 53:03.441
You are loving, gracious, kind, merciful.

53:04.582 --> 53:10.489
What you think of us, you wish this blessing to be upon us.

53:12.312 --> 53:14.354
We're a count to stars.

53:14.946 --> 53:17.751
the thoughts you have towards a still outnumber.

53:18.412 --> 53:19.974
What do you want us to do, Lord?

53:20.495 --> 53:28.008
That's something for each and every one of us, but I think today's message was kind of narrowed.

53:29.410 --> 53:41.650
If that's what you're wanting us to do, to forgive someone, to love somebody, even after what they've done to us, would you give us what's next and how to?

53:42.274 --> 53:44.476
And what can we boldly ask of you, Lord?

53:44.576 --> 53:55.068
I ask that you would give us your spirit, you'd wrap us in your arms of love, you would give us the faith to believe that all these words and promises of God are yes and amen.

53:55.648 --> 54:09.263
And Lord, I'm asking for my brothers and sisters, anyone whose heart has been hurt and ached and maybe whatever the case that Lord, they would know there's no pain that you can heal.

54:10.044 --> 54:11.826
Jacob's gonna see his son.

54:13.698 --> 54:15.221
that heart is going to be healed.

54:16.904 --> 54:18.027
And Lord, we're going to see you.

54:18.047 --> 54:24.159
And we know that we can live in that blessing that we're forgiven.

54:24.600 --> 54:32.155
One day we'll see you, but until that time, Lord, may we all just live and know the peace of a Father who runs to us.

54:32.736 --> 54:34.199
Is that what you're asking us to do?

54:34.219 --> 54:35.922
Then Lord, I pray.

54:36.418 --> 54:40.288
that you would lead the way in our hearts to go do what you've called us to do.

54:40.349 --> 54:41.331
We bless you, Lord.

54:41.672 --> 54:42.334
We love you.

54:42.374 --> 54:43.377
We love your word.

54:43.437 --> 54:45.101
We love the way you speak to us.

54:45.783 --> 54:46.986
And we bless you.

54:47.046 --> 54:50.255
And we simply love you and adore you.

54:50.636 --> 54:52.000
In your name, amen.

54:52.621 --> 54:52.882
Amen.

